
// This Hyperlambda code snippet uses the [add] slot to append nodes to the result of evaluating the expression [@data.connect/*/data.read]. It retrieves nodes specified by the expressions [@.arguments/*/limit] and [@.arguments/*/offset] using the [get-nodes] slot, which are then added to the result set. This pattern is useful for dynamically modifying a node set based on argument values.
add:x:@data.connect/*/data.read
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/limit
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/offset
